-- French Stock Market Regulator to Open LVMH-Hermes Probe, Le Figaro Reports
-- B y   S t e v e   R h i n d s
-- 2010-11-05T05:42:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-05/french-stock-market-regulator-to-open-lvmh-hermes-probe-le-figaro-reports.html
France’s stock market regulator has
decided there are grounds to start an official probe into LVMH
Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton SA’s purchase of a 17 percent stake
in Hermes International SCA, Le Figaro reported, without saying
where it got the information.  The aim of the probe is to ensure that LVMH respected all
the necessary regulations when building its stake, according to
the French daily newspaper.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Steve Rhinds at 
 srhinds@bloomberg.net  